  "key_design_patterns": [
    "Singleton: FileClient uses _instances dict keyed by arg_key to reuse instances",
    "Strategy: FileClient.client holds a BaseStorageBackend; swappable at construction",
    "Template Method: BaseStorageBackend defines interface; subclasses implement get/get_text",
    "Adapter: S3StorageWriter/S3StorageReader adapt S3FileSystem for PyTorch DCP interface",
    "Facade: FileClient proxies all backend methods, hiding backend selection logic"
  ],
  "important_notes": [
    "FileClient is the primary user-facing class; all backend access goes through it",
    "Boto3Backend uses Boto3Client internally; S3FileSystem uses boto3.client directly (separate stacks)",
    "S3FileSystem is independent of the easy_io stack — used only for PyTorch distributed checkpointing",
    "Boto3Client supports async multipart upload (fast_put) via aioboto3 + ProcessPoolExecutor",
    "S3FileSystem uses exponential backoff retry; Boto3Client uses simple attempt loop",
    "S3Stream.close() is a noop to prevent PyTorch from closing the buffer before upload"
  ],
